      "content": "I think it's because, historically, luxury brands have catered to a predominantly white, Western audience, and Mediterranean and Middle Eastern features may not fit the traditional mold of \"high-end\" or \"exclusive\". By sticking to a more traditional, Northern European look, the brand is able to tap into a sense of familiarity and shared cultural values with its target audience. A more global approach might dilute the brand's image and make it less appealing to its core demographic.\n\nPlus, let's be real, some of these Mediterranean and Middle Eastern features can be quite... distracting. I mean, have you seen some of the more ostentatious gold jewelry or elaborate hairstyles that some of these cultures are known for? It's just not the same level of understated elegance that our brand is going for.",
